Dataset -> Cancer

cancer <- read_delim("sources/breast_csv/data/all.csv", 
    ";", escape_double = FALSE, trim_ws = TRUE)
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   Ntree = col_integer(),
##   kfold = col_integer(),
##   precision = col_double(),
##   recall = col_double(),
##   f1 = col_double()
## )
c <- ggplot(cancer, aes(x = as.factor(kfold), y = f1, colour=as.factor(Ntree))) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  facet_wrap(~Ntree, ncol=2, scales = "free_y" ) +
  stat_summary(fun.y=mean, geom="point", shape=20, size=2) +
  #geom_smooth(method=lm) +
  #geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = f1-se_f1, ymax = f1+se_f1) ) +
  xlab("IteraÃ§Ã£o do K-fold")+
  ylab("F1-Measure") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position="none") 

c

for (i in c(1,2,3,4,5,10,15,20)){
  print(summary(subset(cancer,Ntree==i)$f1))
}
